irected by Bill Duke. The film stars Olympia Dukakis, Ellen Burstyn, Diane Ladd and Danny Aiello.", "Anbu Karangal (lit. Hands of love) is a 1965 Indian Tamil film, directed by K. Shankar and produced by N. Periannana. The film stars Sivaji Ganesan, Devika, K. Balaji and Nagesh in lead roles. The film had musical score by R. Sudarsanam.", "Shrewsbury Cemetery, historically known as Camp Parapet Cemetery, is an old burial ground near New Orleans, Louisiana, on the site of a Confederate military camp during the American Civil War. The cemetery is the burying ground of Ross Church and First Zion Church, both located nearby. It is also sometimes known as First Zion Cemetery"]], "steps": [{"stage": "router", "label": "SINGLE_HOP", "raw": "Label: SINGLE_HOP 

